<subSubSection pageId="793" pageNumber="794" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="793" pageNumber="794">
Genus 
<taxonomicName LSID="FFFF5250-3A0A-FF88-2450-FFB66D45FF8E" authority="Dejean, 1825" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1825" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Coptodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Coptodera" order="Coleoptera" pageId="793" pageNumber="794" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Coptodera Dejean, 1825</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="793" pageNumber="794" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="793" pageNumber="794">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1825" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Coptodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="793" pageNumber="794" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Coptodera</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1825: 273. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1825" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Coptodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="793" pageNumber="794" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="festiva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="793" pageNumber="794">Coptodera festiva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1825 designated by Hope (1838: 85). Etymology (original). From the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="793" pageNumber="794">copto</emphasis>
(to cut, chop) and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="793" pageNumber="794">dere</emphasis>
(neck, by extension pronotum), alluding to the straight (i.e., without lobe as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Lebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="793" pageNumber="794" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="793" pageNumber="794">Lebia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) basal edge of the pronotum (&quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="793" pageNumber="794">corselet</emphasis>
... 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="793" pageNumber="794">
<normalizedToken originalValue="coupé">coupe</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="carrément">carrement</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="postérieurement">posterieurement</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
&quot;) of the adult [feminine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="793" pageNumber="794" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="793" pageNumber="794">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="793" pageNumber="794">
About 105 species (Lorenz 2005: 457-458) in the Nearctic (five species), Neotropical (43 species), Australian, Afrotropical, Oriental, and Palaearctic (13 species in eastern Asia only) Regions. These species are arrayed in four subgenera: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1825" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Coptodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="793" pageNumber="794" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="793" pageNumber="794">Coptodera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.str. (about 45 species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Haplocrepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="793" pageNumber="794" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="793" pageNumber="794">Haplocrepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jeannel (six Afrotropical species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Coptoderina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="793" pageNumber="794" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="793" pageNumber="794">Coptoderina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jeannel (53 species), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hansen" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Coptoderinella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="793" pageNumber="794" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="793" pageNumber="794">Coptoderinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hansen (one Afrotropical species).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
